<section id="ignorable">
    <title>(ignorable) sub-unit with the <code>segment</code> flag set to <code>no</code></title>
    <para>Part of the extracted content that is not included in a segment (and therefore not
        translatable). For example tools can use <code>(ignorable)</code> to store the white space
        or codes that are between two segments.</para>
    <para><emphasis>Contains:</emphasis></para>
    <simplelist>
        <member>- One <olink targetdoc="source.xml" targetptr="source"><code>source</code></olink>
            object followed by</member>
        <member>- Zero or one <olink targetdoc="target.xml" targetptr="target"
                ><code>target</code></olink> element</member>
    </simplelist>
    
    <para><emphasis>Properties:</emphasis></para>
    <simplelist>
        <member>- <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/id.xml" targetptr="id"><code>id</code></olink>, <glossterm>optional</glossterm></member>
    </simplelist>
    <itemizedlist>
        <title>LIOM Conformance Requirements</title>
        <listitem><para>LIOM Conformant specifications <glossterm>may</glossterm> omit ordering the
                    <code>source</code> and <code>target</code> objects as long as they provide a
                method to unequivocally discern the <code>source</code> and <code>target</code>
                objects. </para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist> 
    
